PROBLEM: Complete the Singleton class in your editor which contains the following components:

1) A private Singleton non parameterized constructor.
2) A public String instance variable named str.
3) Write a static method named getSingleInstance that returns the single instance of the Singleton class.

LANGUAGE: JAVA

SOL:
import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;
import java.text.*;
import java.math.*;
import java.util.regex.*;
import java.lang.reflect.*;


class Singleton{
    static Singleton instance = new Singleton();
    
    private Singleton() {
        
    }
    
    public String str;
    
    static Singleton getSingleInstance() {
        return instance;
    }

}

INPUT:
hello world
OUTPUT:
Hello I am a singleton! Let me say hello world to you
